  "prompt": "How can I find wps pin on my galaxy S5 connected wifi?",
  "response": "To find the WPS PIN for your Galaxy S5 connected to a Wi-Fi network, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Access Wi-Fi Settings:**\n   - Open the **Settings** app on your Galaxy S5.\n   - Tap on **Connections** (or **Network**).\n   - Select **Wi-Fi**.\n\n2. **Find the Connected Network:**\n   - In the Wi-Fi settings, look for the name of the Wi-Fi network you are connected to. It will be listed at the top under \"Connected\".\n\n3. **View Network Details:**\n   - Tap on the gear icon (\u2699\ufe0f) next to the name of the connected Wi-Fi network.\n   - This will take you to the network details page.\n\n4. **Look for WPS Options:**\n   - Scroll down; you may find options related to **WPS**. If the WPS function is available, you may see an option to connect via WPS. If you need to enter a PIN, it might be listed there.\n\n5. **Check Router:**\n   - Alternatively, if you're unable to find the PIN on your Galaxy S5, you can check your Wi-Fi router. Many routers have a WPS PIN printed on a sticker on the back or bottom.\n   - In some cases, you can access your router's web interface by putting its IP address into a web browser. Look for WPS settings in the router's interface.\n\n### Note:\nIf your network does not have a WPS PIN (if it's been disabled or if your router doesn't support it), you may not find a WPS PIN on your device. Additionally, if your device doesn't allow access to the WPS PIN through the settings, consider using the physical WPS button on the router for connection instead of a PIN.\n\nAlways ensure that any security settings are managed according to good practices to keep your network safe.",
